title: "RosterWise™ — College Sports Recruiting Intelligence App"
description: "The recruiting intelligence app that helps high school athletes and families find the right college program. Deep roster analysis for soccer, lacrosse, volleyball, and more. $40, lifetime access, no subscriptions."
og_type: website
faq:
  - q: "How much does RosterWise cost?"
    a: "$40 one-time purchase. No subscriptions, no monthly fees, no ads. You pay once and get lifetime access for your entire recruiting journey."
  - q: "What sports does RosterWise cover?"
    a: "RosterWise Soccer is available now, covering men's and women's NCAA D1, D2, D3, and NAIA programs. Lacrosse, volleyball, softball, and field hockey are coming soon — each as a separate app."
  - q: "What data does RosterWise analyze?"
    a: "RosterWise analyzes every roster at every program: position depth, class-year composition, international player percentage, recruiting pathway patterns, and academic fit. The app also generates a personalized RosterFit score for every program based on your athlete's profile."
  - q: "How is this different from NCSA, SportsRecruits, or CSPathway?"
    a: "Those platforms are broad but shallow — they list schools and facilitate coach outreach, but they don't tell you anything about who's actually on a roster or how your athlete compares. RosterWise goes deep on roster intelligence: position-by-position analysis, class-year gaps, recruiting patterns, and personalized fit scoring."
  - q: "Do I need to create an account?"
    a: "No. RosterWise does not require an account, login, or registration. Your athlete's profile stays on your device."
  - q: "Is there a refund policy?"
    a: "Yes. Refunds are handled through the App Store or Google Play per their standard refund policies. We also offer direct support at support@grobegames.com."
  - q: "Where does the data come from?"
    a: "RosterWise pulls data from publicly available college athletics roster pages. We update roster data regularly throughout the recruiting cycle. Our data pipeline covers 2,200+ programs across NCAA and NAIA."
  - q: "Is RosterWise available on Android?"
    a: "RosterWise is launching first on iOS (App Store). An Android version is planned. Sign up to be notified when it's available."
  - q: "What is a RosterFit score?"
    a: "RosterFit is RosterWise's proprietary scoring system. It compares your athlete's profile — position, height, class year, geographic preferences, academic profile — against every program's actual roster data to surface the best-fit schools. Higher scores mean stronger alignment."
  - q: "Can RosterWise help with the transfer portal?"
    a: "Transfer portal intelligence is on our roadmap. The current version focuses on high school-to-college recruiting."
